  "contentData": [
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "216ea22b-01af-4645-8972-5766bbd75b6c",
      "udi": "umb://element/469d4074fd7c4fcb97f877ad0f01716a",
      "title": "Course content/modules",
      "content": "<p>A degree in Business Management has been offered by QMU for decades. We regularly review course content and options to ensure students are provided with an up-to-date learning experience which is relevant to current trends in business management. </p>"
    },
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "216ea22b-01af-4645-8972-5766bbd75b6c",
      "udi": "umb://element/3fc2efacf78f42c1959cc646005b921a",
      "title": "Teaching, learning and assessment ",
      "content": "<p>You will be taught in lectures, seminars and practical workshops. Outside these timetabled sessions you will be expected to continue learning through self-study.</p>\n<p>Please also visit the <a href=\"/{localLink:umb://document/363407ed108f454784361ca7c9d57713}\" title=\"How we teach and how you'll learn - Undergraduate\">How you teach and how you'll learn</a> page.</p>"
    },
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "216ea22b-01af-4645-8972-5766bbd75b6c",
      "udi": "umb://element/bcc4c2b66b424eaab12779e5e934f195",
      "title": "Careers",
      "content": "<p>You will already be employed, so you won’t suddenly hit the job market like most graduates do. You will be able to take the theoretical understanding you have learnt in your degree and apply it directly to challenges in your workplace. From there, your goal will be to use your new skills to step your career up to the next level.</p>"
    },
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "216ea22b-01af-4645-8972-5766bbd75b6c",
      "udi": "umb://element/7dc5124347234f778f1cc0a3864bc17d",
      "title": "Entry requirements",
      "content": "<p>Scottish Higher: BBBC</p>\n<p>The course is available if you are currently living and working in Scotland and working on a full-time or part-time basis.</p>\n<p>You can apply if you are aged 16 or over and there is no maximum age limit.</p>\n<p>If you have already completed a degree with SAAS funding, you could still do a GA, particularly if it is a career change to something new.</p>\n<p>If you are a school leaver or not in employment but think that a GA could be for you, you can apply the same way you would apply for a job. The vacancies are advertised on the <a href=\"https://www.apprenticeships.scot/\" title=\"Apprenticeships Scotland\">Apprenticeships Scotland website</a>.</p>\n<p>Typically, we would expect a minimum of four Scottish Highers (or equivalent).</p>\n<p>Your application will be assessed on an individual basis, taking into account any previous industry experience you may have. If you have already completed a Foundation or Modern Apprenticeship in a related subject, this will also contribute towards meeting the entry requirements.</p>\n<p>If you are interested in applying, please email: <a href=\"mailto:%20ga@qmu.ac.uk\">ga@qmu.ac.uk</a> in the first instance.</p>\n<p>Am I a <strong>Widening Access</strong> student?: We apply the minimum entry criteria to applicants who meet one or more contextual factor. To see if this would apply to you, please refer to the <a href=\"/study-here/access-to-higher-education/application-and-access/\">access and application</a> page.</p>"
    },
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "216ea22b-01af-4645-8972-5766bbd75b6c",
      "udi": "umb://element/2a86015e6bdb47fb885b49e4cae2336f",
      "title": "Teaching staff, class sizes and timetables",
      "content": "<p>For more information, please visit ‘<a href=\"/{localLink:umb://document/363407ed108f454784361ca7c9d57713}\" title=\"How we teach and how you'll learn - Undergraduate\">How we teach and how you’ll learn</a>’.</p>"
    },
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "216ea22b-01af-4645-8972-5766bbd75b6c",
      "udi": "umb://element/01f457bc841a4abbaa1875d0ac998d40",
      "title": "Placements",
      "content": "<p>You will continue to work in your current role while you study. This will help you develop your learning into practical, real-world business expertise.</p>"
    },
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "216ea22b-01af-4645-8972-5766bbd75b6c",
      "udi": "umb://element/2c1dc1da2f914596858ccb95371ae187",
      "title": "Application",
      "content": "<p>Before applying for this course, please email <a href=\"mailto:%20GA@qmu.ac.uk\">GA@qmu.ac.uk </a>in the first instance to discuss your application. We just need to make sure you meet the criteria and that your employer is happy for you to apply to be a Graduate Apprentice.</p>"
    },
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "216ea22b-01af-4645-8972-5766bbd75b6c",
      "udi": "umb://element/d17852e4ce9d4e08aa0de2a3e1a99b67",
      "title": "Awarding body",
      "content": "<p>QMU. More information is in the ‘External Review’ section of the <a href=\"/{localLink:umb://document/363407ed108f454784361ca7c9d57713}\" title=\"How we teach and how you'll learn - Undergraduate\">How we teach and how you'll learn</a> page.</p>"
    },
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "216ea22b-01af-4645-8972-5766bbd75b6c",
      "udi": "umb://element/3f72afd69ee94b4aaabb6dc5c174998b",
      "title": "Fees",
      "content": "<p>Graduate Apprenticeship students apply to SAAS for their fees to be paid.</p>"
    }
  ],
